title: D-Day - The Invasion March To Victory - 3 part Documentary
description:
D-Day: The Invasion March to Victory

May 8, 1945...V.E. Day, Victory in Europe.  After years of struggle, a deserved celebration.  But how did the Allies do it?  How did they defeat Adolph Hitler's massively powerful army?  What was the turning point?  The answer to this question is the landing at Normandy.  The most important battle the Allies and German's ever fought...and they called it, D-Day.

Follow the events and milestones leading up to this historic day in this prolific documentary program featuring rare and never-before-seen archival video footage and insightful narration.

Winston Churchill Part 1 & 2

Winston Churchill was truly a renaissance man.  He was a journalist, historian, political leader and painter and was the personification of tenacity.  He continually managed to regain his position after enduring numerous political defeats.  This intimate portrait of Winston Churchill allows us to better understand one of the great individuals of the 20th Century.
